The paper proposes a deep learning-based model for spatio-temporal prediction, which involves learning complex and non-linear relationships in data that is highly influenced by external factors. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with spatio-temporal data, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
